<br />
<br />I got the idea of making kits from this video.<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MblnbUURHjY">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MblnbUURHjY</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I want to make an easy plastic kit to assemble. To order just the arcade box from him cost 70 dollars. If I can get a good mold I could charge way less. 
<br />
<br />I have never solder before but have watched many video's. I know I will mess up a few time, but I figured if I bought the right tools from the start it would be much easier. 
<br />
<br />I could make cases and other objects with the former. Just need to know what people need. 
<br />
<br />I recently traded a stormtrooper armor for 400 nes games. I was thinking about offering them for sale to be made in reproductions. 
<br />
<br />My wife was kind enough to buy me a vacuum chamber and pressure pot to do custom casting. This is another outlet I have.

		

